      <p>O LamLam, originally from Hong Kong and now based in Kyoto. O uses various mediums like film, installations, and performances to create multiple ways of narratives. She has been experimenting with the ways in which ethnicity specific to regions and races is "translated". Through her work &lt;Change: Positive, satisfying, and nothing&gt; and &lt;Ein süßer Traum unter der Erde&gt;, she redefined nationality and history, reality and fiction. This experimentation examines what kinds of "mistranslations" or changes occur in the process. This experimentation examines what kinds of mistranslations or changes occur in the process within creating a new story by these facts. Her work aims to reshape narratives and create a multi-verse of stories.</p>
